cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

The paper deals with domain adaptation in computer vision tasks such as image classification, object detection, and object category recognition. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel domain adaptation method that leverages multiple target domains, which involves machine learning techniques such as structural SVM (SSVM) classifiers. This suggests that the paper could also belong to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper applies the proposed method to pedestrian detection and object category recognition, which are specific applications of computer vision, indicating that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
